{
    "name": "Malenti",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The unpredictability and viciousness of the sahuagin race isn\u2019t just an aspect of their sharklike temperament\u2014 it seems to be inherent in their very beings. The unusual and typically deadly mutants common to the race attest to this, their forms altering and becoming more deadly based either on the needs of the community or ambiguous environmental factors. Whatever the case, sahuagin mutants often rise to positions of respect and inf luence in sahuagin communities, their innate advantages instantly placing them among their people\u2019s rulers. Of these mutants, four-armed sahuagin brutes and malenti\u2014 sahuagin with the appearances of sea elves\u2014arise most commonly, though these are in no way the only sahuagin mutants known to the savage seas."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>A predatory gleam glints in the eyes of this stern-looking aquatic elf.</i>",
